Projects.Title: Taxi Fare Prediction Project - Machine Learning
Projects.Description: This project highlights my expertise in applying machine learning to real-world predictive analytics challenges within the transportation industry. I developed a robust model capable of accurately predicting taxi fares based on a variety of features, leveraging advanced machine learning algorithms. Engineered an advanced predictive model using ensemble methods, significantly improving the accuracy of taxi fare predictions. Trained on a large dataset of taxi trips, the model incorporated temporal, contextual features to enhance prediction reliability.

Projects.Title: Diabetes Prediction - Machine Learning
Projects.Description: This project showcases my capability to apply machine learning techniques to the healthcare domain, specifically focusing on predicting diabetes based on various health indicators. The project involved developing a predictive model that accurately determines the likelihood of diabetes in patients, leveraging advanced machine learning algorithms and data analysis techniques. Engineered a predictive model using logistic regression, decision trees, and ensemble methods, improving prediction accuracy by 15%. The model was trained on a comprehensive dataset that included features such as age, BMI, blood pressure, and glucose levels. This project emphasized data preprocessing, feature selection, model tuning, and validation, demonstrating a robust application of machine learning in healthcare analytics.
